Are three ever updates? I would like to be able to save the settings made

informed me that saving the different conditions were VERY save able. There

app!
replyContent: The settings for each "thing" (options/plane/scenery/controller/joystick/lighting) are saved separately as copies of the original. So if you modify a plane, save it, then when you load the plane either find it at the bottom (keep scrolling!) or use the "user" tab.

replyContent:
In 3D sceneries you can change the spawn location: In settings-options 2 tick "Enable walkabout button". Back in "game", use the "walking figure" button - move the spawn point with the on-screen sticks.

Pick a suitable plane for the location & everything is OK - people don't launch prop planes on steep slopes - gliders are more fun anyway!

replyContent: Yes you're right - you can't do full mixing with the in-app settings - I just thought it would be too complicated to be practical! The mixing is done in the aeroplane configuration files - you can actually get these from the Windows version, adjust the mixing (or anything you like), then add them to the Android app as user files.

I spent many years flying radio control in my youth. I really missed my sail planes and slope soaring, this game is very close to the real thing. One addition I would like to see is competition soaring with the landing stripe and bulls eye.
Brilliant :)

... my Moga (the first and most popular Android controller) still appears to not be supported but apparently others are via OTG I feel like it's all but perfect :)  5 stars then since it definiately deserves more than 4.
replyContent: It now supports controllers using USB OTG - should work with gamepads and R/C Transmitters (with USB interface). Android has some resolution problems, so it will work better with devices that are by default pretty much calibrated. Let me know if there's any problems (or if it works for you!).

content: I fly rc and I am amazed at the flight dynamics that just feel right. I only wish you could add the feel of batteries beginning to loose power.
Only giving four star because I cant change the camera angle. Otherwise 5 stars
replyContent: You can change the camera in the 3D sceneries (they're the not-so-pretty ones!). There's no way to move the camera in the panoramic ones, unfortunately.

content: Absolutely the best simulator I have ever flown. This will make training new people much easier.

I keep coming back to this.  If I want a challenge I go fly the plank off a cliff, but if like tonight I just want to relax I just fly the trainer lazily around the hills.  I can't say I'm very good yet or ever will be - just love it though.
It's like to fly a real plane!

Ive loved the free version to death.  And now I've learnt to use it I'm purchasing the full version.  This is a seriously awesome slope glider sim. I've just this morning learnt how to dynamic soar with the sailplane, and whizzing around the hills at 357mph never gets tired.  Physics are amazing,  and as I can't get to my local slope too often,  this really is a great replacement.  Slopers you will love this.  Congrats on a super app rowlhouse!
amazing physics...  one of the best flight sims out there.
Great work ,my fav sim...
replyContent: Thanks :)

content: I love gliders and free flight planes in real life. This is the best app for when I can't get out in the field.
My favorite app for passing the time!

This app is so well done. From the physics to the adjustability it's just perfect. Enjoyed it so much I made an RC glider and chase seagulls around on the dunes by my house. This made the transition to rc flight so simple and painless and it's a blast to play when the winds are crap out here. I've used just about every flight sim out there and this is the first one to even come close to the sensation of actually flying. If you don't love this app flying probably just isn't for you.
replyContent: Thanks for the review - hearing that it got you out flying gliders for real has made my day!

content: Awesome game not easy to do just like the real thing but it don't cost loads to repair unlike the real thing a must for r/c flyers novice and experienced

This game is awesome, it is actually so much more than just a game. I see some people rating the free version with not a lot of stars because it has not too many planes or the scenarios or even because the planes have no motor and it is hard to control, this game is an Remote control pilot simulator oriented for slope gliders and thermal gliders, thats why you must use the two cross inputs. I love playing it, the physics are so real it is unbeleivable! I felt like this was my first plane before throwing my own slope glider into the wind! Good Game Rowlhouse!
